import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'])
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['price'], vert=False, showfliers=True, whis=1.5, widths=0.7, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), medianprops=dict(color='black'), flierprops=dict(marker='o', markerfacecolor='red', markersize=5, linestyle='none', alpha=0.5))
    ax.set_xlabel('Price')
    ax.set_yticklabels(['Price'])
    ax.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["price"].mean():0.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average daily closing price of the S&P 500 index?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the daily closing prices of the S&P 500 index?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['date'], data['price'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    data['rolling_mean'] = data['price'].rolling(window=30).mean()
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'], label='Price')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['rolling_mean'], label='30-day Moving Average')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the volatility of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
